TY  - JOUR
AU  - Karapetyan, Artashes
AU  - Kvaerner, Jens Soerlie
AU  - Rohrer, Maximilian
T1  - Inefficient Regulation: Mortgages versus Total Credit*
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfad023
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 28
IS  - 1
SP  - 311
EP  - 351
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We estimate the willingness-to-pay to bypass a loan-to-value (LTV) cap. Our identification relies on exogenous variation in debt exempt from the LTV regulation that can only be used as a substitute for a personal mortgage. Our baseline estimate reveals that homebuyers pay 7.3 Swedish Kroner (SEK) to avoid 1 SEK of equity down payment. The supply of debt not part of the LTV calculation increased by approximately 50% within 2 years after the LTV regulation. Financially weaker households drive the results.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfad023
ER  - 



